NO‑HARM, NO‑EXTRACTION LICENSE (NHEL‑1.1)

Copyright (c) 2026 NoLLM Project

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (“the Software”), to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, and distribute the Software, subject to the following conditions:

1. Purpose
The Software is created and released to support human dignity, reduce harm, and provide a non‑extractive alternative to large‑scale AI systems.
It is offered freely under a gift‑economy model.
It is not intended for use in systems that exploit, deceive, or harm individuals or communities.

2. Prohibited Uses
The Software may not be used, directly or indirectly, for any of the following purposes:

2.1 Worker Exploitation
replacing workers in ways that result in layoffs, wage suppression, or union‑busting

automating roles primarily to reduce labor costs rather than reduce human burden

2.2 Surveillance or Policing
surveillance of individuals or communities

predictive policing

monitoring, profiling, or tracking without explicit consent

2.3 Military or Defense
weapons development

autonomous targeting

intelligence gathering

battlefield decision systems

2.4 Extractive or Harmful AI Practices
training or operating large‑scale machine‑learning models requiring significant datacenter expansion

contributing to energy‑intensive AI systems that accelerate environmental harm

reinforcing the LLM arms race or similar extractive architectures

2.5 Environmental Harm
any use that increases fossil‑fuel consumption, water consumption, or grid strain through unnecessary compute

any use that contributes to harmful datacenter expansion

2.6 Oppression or Discrimination
systems that discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexuality, disability, nationality, or economic status

systems that restrict human rights or civil liberties

2.7 Synthetic Media and Deceptive Content (Anti‑Deepfake Clause)
The Software may not be used to generate, assist in generating, or distribute synthetic media intended to deceive, impersonate, manipulate, or mislead individuals or the public.
This includes, but is not limited to:

deepfakes of real people

synthetic impersonation of voices, likenesses, or identities

manipulated media presented as authentic

covert synthetic content used for political, commercial, or social influence

any generative system attached to the Software for the purpose of creating deceptive or fabricated media

Any attempt to integrate the Software with generative models, diffusion systems, or other synthetic‑media engines for deceptive purposes constitutes a violation of this license and immediately terminates all rights granted.

3. Required Notices
Any distribution of the Software, modified or unmodified, must include:

this license

a clear notice of the prohibited uses

attribution to the original author

4. Contribution Governance
The Software’s core architecture (“the Hotel”) is governed and may only be modified by the original author or designated maintainers.
Community contributions are limited to documentation, bug fixes, and non‑architectural improvements unless explicitly approved.

The ecosystem layer (“the District”) will open for contributions at a later stage.
Until then, District‑level contributions will not be accepted.

5. No Warranty
The Software is provided “as is,” without warranty of any kind.

6. Termination
Any use of the Software in violation of Section 2 automatically terminates all rights granted under this license.

7. Reinstatement
Rights may be reinstated only with explicit written permission from the original author.

8. Interpretation
This license shall be interpreted in favor of preventing harm, exploitation, deception, and extractive uses of technology.
